<div id="review_764068223" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/764068223" />
    <a title="Clare O&#39;Beara" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/23233462-clare-o-beara"><img alt="Clare O&#39;Beara" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1585485276p2/23233462.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/764068223?book_show_action=true">Nov 13, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Clare O&#39;Beara" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Clare O&#39;Beara" href="/user/show/23233462-clare-o-beara">Clare O&#39;Beara</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/23233462-clare-o-beara?shelf=british-historical">british-historical</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/23233462-clare-o-beara?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer764068223" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5536013888409854288">This ends the Arthurian trilogy which was very well written and full of lively characters. <br/>I thought that the end was too sad, and that the fact that the kingdom had held out against the Dark Ages for just long enough for the monks from Ireland to collect and save all the books, was not stressed enough. This is a personal story told by the Guinevere character, who fell for a trick and for the wrong person. <br/>My favourite is the first book Hawk of May. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


