        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer813304728" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3775155987975516868">The heartbreaking ending to an unforgettable retelling of the Arthurian legend. Even though I read the first two books in the series many times over, I did not have the courage to read this third one a second time...the beauty and sadness were overwhelming. The only other time I felt this way about the ending of a series was when I closed The Return of the King by J.R.R. Tolkien. I&apos;m going to go through the series again, and this time, I will read all three. Be strong, my heart.</span>
  <span id="freeText3775155987975516868" style="display:none">The heartbreaking ending to an unforgettable retelling of the Arthurian legend. Even though I read the first two books in the series many times over, I did not have the courage to read this third one a second time...the beauty and sadness were overwhelming. The only other time I felt this way about the ending of a series was when I closed The Return of the King by J.R.R. Tolkien. I'm going to go through the series again, and this time, I will read all three. Be strong, my heart.</span>
